Plot purposes aside, Hunter’s Moon serves several simultaneous narrative functions. The first is being a foil for both Moon Knight and Zodiac. A “foil” is a character whose traits are meant to highlight another’s, usually but not always antagonists…

…and Harry and Draco (Harry’s heroic reputation contrasts with Draco’s villainous one). A foiled pair does not necessarily have to be antagonistic towards each other (Steve and Bucky were friends), but it’s more common than not that they are.
@carexcs hii, let's be moots!

Examples of narrative foils include Steve Rogers and Bucky Barnes (both as superheroes and as normal people pre-WWII), Eren and Reiner from AOT (Eren’s drive for freedom contrasts with Reiner’s devotion to carry out his mission)…

Hunter’s Moon, though fighting for the same purpose, contrasts with just about everything in regards to Moon Knight. Though both were given the choice between servitude and death, Dr. Badr willfully serves Khonshu while Marc Spector is disillusioned.
